MCSettings.Name: Revit Model Health Dashboard
MCSettings.Author: Autodesk
MCSettings.Description: Series of checks to review modeling best practices and integrity

Heading.Description: Checks that have been created but not placed in the structure yet.

Section.Title: Checks that have not been placed

Section.Description: Checks in this section relate to and can directly impact model performance, when not managed properly.

Check.Description: Reports all warnings in a Revit model.
Reports the file size of a Revit model in MB (megabytes).
Reports the number of elements that can be purged from a Revit model.
Lists all user worksets for a Revit model or reports '*Not Workshared*' if worksharing is not enabled. Also optionally lists the number of instances in each workset.
Lists all Design Options in a Revit model. Also optionally lists the number of instances in each design option.
COUNT of redundantly placed instances of the same element in the model. Elements in the same "physical" space in a model can severely impact performance and lead to issues.
Check.FailureMessage: Element is a duplicate at the same location and base level.

Check.Description: COUNT of all instances of Revit Linked Files in the model. Linked files can impact model performance.
COUNT of all linked CAD files in the model.
COUNT of imported CAD files in the model. Imported geometry can impact model size and performance.
Will report the number of imported SKP files.
COUNT of imported images placed in the model.
Lists all non built-in categories and sub-categories in a Revit model.
COUNT of views in the model. Views typically do not impact model size, but too many unmanaged views can impact user efficiency and overridden elements in views can impact performance.
COUNT of sheets in the model. Sheets typically do not impact model size, but too many unmanaged views can impact user efficiency.
Reports the number of views (not including views that can be placed on more than one sheet, like Schedules and Legends) that are not placed on a sheet.
Lists all views in a Revit model that have permanently hidden model elements and the total number of hidden elements.
COUNT of of placed instances of Model Groups in the model. Too many model groups can be an indication of improper modeling techniques.
COUNT of placed instances of Detail Groups in the model. Too many detail groups can be an indication of improper modeling techniques.
COUNT of placed instances of In-Place Families in the model. In-place families can signifcantly impact model size and performance and should be used sparingly.
Count of placed elements in the model for Revit 2017. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between version.
Count of placed elements in the model for Revit 2018. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between version.
Count of placed elements in the model for Revit 2019. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between version.
Count of placed elements in the model for Revit 2020. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between version.
Count of placed elements in the model for Revit 2021. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between version.
Count of placed elements in the model for Revit 2022. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between version.
Count of placed elements in the model for Revit 2023. This check is version specific due to changes in Revit categories between version.
